---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Best Camera Lenses (2026) — cameraupick" description="Complete lens buying guides for Sony E-mount, Canon RF, and Fujifilm X-mount cameras. Find the perfect lens for portraits, video, travel, and more.">
<main class="container">
    <section class="hero">
            <div class="hero-grid">
                <div>
                    <h1>Camera Lens Buying Guides</h1>
                    <p class="hero-sub">
                        The right lens transforms your photography. We test lenses for sharpness, autofocus speed, video
                        performance, and value.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="hero-media">
                    <picture>
                        <source srcset="/assets/images/guides/lenses-hero.webp" type="image/webp">
                        <img src="/assets/images/guides/lenses-hero.jpg" alt="Camera lenses collection"
                            loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="1400" height="900"
                            style="width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; border-radius: 12px;">
                    </picture>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Lens Guides by Camera Brand</h2>
            <p class="section-sub">Choose your camera system to see our top lens picks</p>

            <div class="grid">
                <article class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;">
                    <h3>Sony E-Mount</h3>
                    <p>The largest lens ecosystem. From budget Sigma primes to premium G Master glass — there's a lens
                        for every budget and style.</p>
                    <div class="meta">Best for: ZV-E10, A6700, A7 series</div>
                    <div style="margin-top: 16px;">
                        <a href="best-sony-e-mount-lenses.html" class="btn-buy">View Sony Lenses →</a>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid #ef4444;">
                    <h3>Canon RF Mount</h3>
                    <p>Canon's new mirrorless system. Premium optics with excellent autofocus, but limited third-party
                        options (for now).</p>
                    <div class="meta">Best for: R50, R8, R6 II, R5</div>
                    <div style="margin-top: 16px;">
                        <a href="best-canon-rf-lenses.html" class="btn-buy">View Canon Lenses →</a>
                    </div>
                </article>

                <article class="card" style="border-left: 4px solid #10b981;">
                    <h3>Fujifilm X-Mount</h3>
                    <p>Compact, sharp, and stylish. Fuji's lenses are designed to match their retro bodies perfectly.
                        Great prime selection.</p>
                    <div class="meta">Best for: X-T5, X-T50, X-S20</div>
                    <div style="margin-top: 16px;">
                        <a href="best-fujifilm-x-mount-lenses.html" class="btn-buy">View Fuji Lenses →</a>
                    </div>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Understanding Lens Basics</h2>
            <div class="grid">
                <article class="card">
                    <h3>Focal Length</h3>
                    <p><strong>Wide (16-35mm):</strong> Landscapes, architecture, vlogging<br>
                        <strong>Standard (35-50mm):</strong> Everyday, street photography<br>
                        <strong>Portrait (85-135mm):</strong> Beautiful background blur<br>
                        <strong>Telephoto (70-200mm+):</strong> Sports, wildlife
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="card">
                    <h3>Aperture (f-number)</h3>
                    <p><strong>f/1.4-f/2:</strong> Amazing low light, creamy bokeh, expensive<br>
                        <strong>f/2.8:</strong> Professional standard, good balance<br>
                        <strong>f/4:</strong> Lighter, cheaper, still great for most uses<br>
                        <strong>f/5.6+:</strong> Variable zooms, budget friendly
                    </p>
                </article>

                <article class="card">
                    <h3>Prime vs Zoom</h3>
                    <p><strong>Prime lenses:</strong> Fixed focal length, sharper, faster apertures, lighter,
                        cheaper<br>
                        <strong>Zoom lenses:</strong> Versatile, one lens for many situations, heavier, more expensive
                        for fast apertures
                    </p>
                </article>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section">
            <h2>Starter Lens Recommendations</h2>
            <div class="comparison-table-wrapper">
                <table class="comparison">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th>Use Case</th>
                            <th>Sony</th>
                            <th>Canon</th>
                            <th>Fujifilm</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>All-Around Zoom</strong></td>
                            <td>Tamron 17-70mm f/2.8</td>
                            <td>Canon RF-S 18-150mm</td>
                            <td>Fuji XF 18-55mm f/2.8-4</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Portrait Prime</strong></td>
                            <td>Sigma 56mm f/1.4</td>
                            <td>Canon RF 50mm f/1.8</td>
                            <td>Fuji XF 56mm f/1.2</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Budget Wide</strong></td>
                            <td>Sony 11mm f/1.8</td>
                            <td>Canon RF-S 10-18mm</td>
                            <td>Fuji XF 16mm f/2.8</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Video All-Rounder</strong></td>
                            <td>Sony 16-55mm f/2.8 G</td>
                            <td>Canon RF 24-105mm f/4</td>
                            <td>Sigma 18-50mm f/2.8</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="section" id="affiliate">
            <h2>Why Trust Our Lens Reviews?</h2>
            <p class="section-sub">
                We test every lens with real-world shooting — not just lab charts. We evaluate autofocus speed, video
                breathing, build quality, and value for money. No manufacturer sponsorships.
            </p>
        </section>

    </main>
</BaseLayout>
